endemo2.output.output_utility module

This module contains utility functions and classes to more easily generate output files.

class FileGenerator(input_manager, directory, filename, output_path=None)[source]

Bases: object

A tool to more easily generate output files.

Variables:

  • input_manager (Input) – A reference to the input_manager that holds all preprocessing.

  • excel_writer (pd.ExcelWriter) – The excel writer used for writing the file.

  • current_sheet_name (str) – Keeps track of the current sheet name that new entries (add_entry) will be written to.

  • current_out_dict (dict) – Keeps the entries that are added. When writing the file, these are converted to a table.

  • out_file_path (str) – The output file path. Mainly used as attribute for debugging.

plot_coef_in_range(label, start_end, coef, color_lin, color_log, color_quadr, color_exp)[source]

Adds all possible functions of a coefficient object to a plot.

Parameters:

  • label (str) – What the coefficients represent.

  • start_end ((int, int)) – The range, that the function should be plotted within.

  • coef (Coef) – The coef object that should be plotted.

  • color_lin – The line color of the linear function.

  • color_quadr – The line color of the quadratic function.

  • color_exp – The line color of the exponential function.

plot_coef_with_method_in_range(label, start_end, coef, color)[source]

Adds the function of a coefficient object with chosen method to the current plot.

Parameters:

  • label (str) – What the coefficients represent.

  • start_end ((int, int)) – The range, that the function should be plotted within.

  • coef (Coef) – The coef object, whose chosen method function should be plotted.

  • color – The color of the line of the function.

plot_historical_data(tds, color, label)[source]

Add the data of a TwoDseries to a plot. If there is only one data point, a dot is plotted, else a line over the whole data.

Parameters:

  • tds (TwoDseries) – The series whose historical data should be plotted.

  • color – The color of the plotted historical data.

  • label – The label for the historical data line.

save_multiple_series_plot(input_manager, folder, tdss, labels, x_label, y_label, back_label, front_label)[source]

Plots multiple TwoDseries into the same image and saves the plot.

Parameters:

  • input_manager (InputManager) – The input_manager to get the output path from.

  • folder – The path, relative to the output folder, the result should be saved to.

  • tdss ([<class 'endemo2.data_structures.prediction_models.TwoDseries'>]) – The TwoDseries that should be plotted.

  • labels ([<class 'str'>]) – The labels for all TwoDseries in order.

  • x_label (str) – The label for the x-axis.

  • y_label (str) – The label for the y-axis.

  • front_label (str) – Label used at the front of the image name and file name.

  • back_label (str) – Label used at the back of the image name and file name.

save_plot(image_label, x_label, y_label, directory, file_name)[source]

Sets the image and axis labels and saves the current plot to the given directory as filename.

Parameters:

  • image_label – The label of the image.

  • x_label – The label of the x-axis.

  • y_label – The label of the y-axis.

  • directory – The directory to save the plot into.

  • file_name – The filename to save the plot as.
